The paper deals with web data mining and information retrieval, which are key topics in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the identification of web sources that publish information relevant to a trend before others, which involves analyzing the content of web pages and identifying patterns, making it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to identify trends, which is relevant to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the approach on real data, which involves the use of machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category.
